WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:02.402 --> 00:00:06.897
<i>Carroll was convicted in 2004 for
the murders of 14 young women.</i>

2
00:00:07.074 --> 00:00:08.634
We need you in Virginia. Ryan.

3
00:00:08.775 --> 00:00:09.975
I'm not an agent anymore.

4
00:00:10.143 --> 00:00:12.510
You caught Carroll. No
one knows him like you do.

5
00:00:12.679 --> 00:00:16.047
- What's my sequel about?
- We're gonna write this together. Ryan.

6
00:00:17.784 --> 00:00:19.810
Even though you
slept with my wife.

7
00:00:19.987 --> 00:00:23.480
I have so many
surprises waiting for you.

8
00:00:24.591 --> 00:00:26.526
Cults. my specialty.

9
00:00:26.693 --> 00:00:28.594
Gay neighbors. The nanny.

10
00:00:28.795 --> 00:00:30.889
How do they figure
into your new plot?

11
00:00:31.064 --> 00:00:32.498
Why is my dad such a bad man?

12
00:00:32.666 --> 00:00:34.225
Maybe he's not so bad.

13
00:00:38.572 --> 00:00:40.939
- Hey. where are you going. huh?
- You're a liar.

14
00:00:42.743 --> 00:00:45.212
- What the hell?
- Hey. guys. this is Megan.

15
00:00:45.379 --> 00:00:46.870
<i>I never killed anything before.</i>

16
00:00:47.047 --> 00:00:48.379
<i>We're just getting started.</i>

17
00:00:48.549 --> 00:00:50.108
They're teaching him.

18
00:00:50.717 --> 00:00:52.845
Why did your
husband try to kill you?

19
00:00:53.020 --> 00:00:57.788
Rick can be scary
when he wants to be.

20
00:00:57.958 --> 00:00:59.119
So who has Joey?

21
00:00:59.326 --> 00:01:01.591
- I don't know where the kid is.
- Does Rick know?

22
00:01:01.762 --> 00:01:03.788
- I don't know. but his wife does.
- What?

23
00:01:03.964 --> 00:01:06.331
Maggie. PARKER: Maggie
Kester is one of them.

24
00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:14.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

25
00:01:15.976 --> 00:01:17.103
How you doing?

26
00:01:18.445 --> 00:01:19.469
Sleep all right?

27
00:01:19.646 --> 00:01:21.137
What are we gonna do. Paul?

28
00:01:21.348 --> 00:01:24.045
You've really screwed up here.

29
00:01:24.217 --> 00:01:26.448
I think we've all
made mistakes. Jacob.

30
00:01:27.220 --> 00:01:29.485
Mistakes are important.
it's how we learn.

31
00:01:29.656 --> 00:01:31.591
But you have gone
off the deep end.

32
00:01:31.758 --> 00:01:33.818
That is an understatement.

33
00:01:33.994 --> 00:01:35.758
Megan. you remember Emma.

34
00:01:37.497 --> 00:01:40.433
Look. she's not very friendly.
Just don't take it personally.

35
00:01:41.001 --> 00:01:43.334
I thought you were gonna deal with this.
- Funny.

36
00:01:43.503 --> 00:01:46.496
- When has he ever dealt with anything?
- Will you stop it?

37
00:01:48.275 --> 00:01:50.676
Who is she? Where
did she come from?

38
00:01:50.877 --> 00:01:53.642
We met in a little grocery
store one town over.

39
00:01:53.814 --> 00:01:55.942
You fool. This is
going to get us caught.

40
00:01:56.116 --> 00:01:57.641
Girls go missing all the time.

41
00:01:57.818 --> 00:01:59.787
Was there a surveillance camera?

42
00:01:59.953 --> 00:02:03.788
No. you didn't think about that. You
will be identified. It's a matter of time.

43
00:02:03.957 --> 00:02:06.188
We're wanted in 50
states. Emma. Who cares?

44
00:02:06.793 --> 00:02:09.262
They won't find this farm
in the middle of nowhere.

45
00:02:09.429 --> 00:02:11.591
Emma's right. This is not cool.

46
00:02:11.765 --> 00:02:16.032
Wow. Jacob. thanks for pointing
out an uncool situation. That helps.

47
00:02:16.203 --> 00:02:17.694
Told you.

48
00:02:18.405 --> 00:02:21.637
First things first. we can't have
Joey see her so get rid of her.

49
00:02:21.808 --> 00:02:25.210
Kill her and bury her out behind
that stable or barn. whatever it is.

50
00:02:30.784 --> 00:02:32.514
All right. sounds like a plan.

51
00:02:34.788 --> 00:02:38.691
Jacob. you kill Megan and I'll make
breakfast. I'm thinking pancakes.

52
00:02:38.859 --> 00:02:42.318
Megan. do you like pancakes?
Oh. wait. sorry. you'll be dead.

53
00:02:42.929 --> 00:02:44.898
Denise? Where are you?

54
00:02:45.065 --> 00:02:48.058
Damn it. Just do it.

55
00:02:51.571 --> 00:02:52.869
What are you doing. Paul?

56
00:02:53.040 --> 00:02:55.009
No. Jacob. what are you doing?

57
00:02:55.876 --> 00:02:58.471
How long do you think
you're gonna get away with it?

58
00:02:58.645 --> 00:03:02.548
Because I. for one.
am tired of all the lies.

59
00:03:14.227 --> 00:03:15.889
<i>Say bye-bye.</i>

60
00:03:16.063 --> 00:03:19.363
You got hardwood.
barn. fences. a farmhouse.

61
00:03:21.034 --> 00:03:22.935
- Have you got it?
<i>- Analyzing it now.</i>

62
00:03:23.103 --> 00:03:26.870
Northern red oak trees and tall fescues
grass in the yard. puts us East Coast.

63
00:03:27.040 --> 00:03:29.202
Trying to pull a number
from the telephone pole.

64
00:03:29.376 --> 00:03:31.538
<i>What about the e-mail
the video was sent from?</i>

65
00:03:31.712 --> 00:03:33.772
An open IP address
courtesy of North Korea.

66
00:03:33.980 --> 00:03:36.100
- Changing the routing.
<i>- They're watching news.</i>

67
00:03:36.183 --> 00:03:38.618
They know we got
Rick and his cell phone.

68
00:03:39.920 --> 00:03:41.684
How are you doing?

69
00:03:43.857 --> 00:03:45.485
I'm good.

70
00:03:45.726 --> 00:03:46.750
All good here.

71
00:03:46.927 --> 00:03:48.361
Keep me posted.

72
00:03:49.563 --> 00:03:51.794
This is... It's helpful.

73
00:03:52.532 --> 00:03:54.797
You know. they made
this video for shock value.

74
00:03:55.001 --> 00:03:57.470
Joe's playing with us.
It's like a game to him.

75
00:03:57.637 --> 00:04:01.574
There's no concrete evidence to support
psychopathic behavior is hereditary.

76
00:04:01.742 --> 00:04:05.406
You think I don't know that? I
know my son's not a psychopath.

77
00:04:05.579 --> 00:04:09.107
Put heroin in someone enough. they
become a junkie. These people are killers.

78
00:04:09.282 --> 00:04:11.046
- Why can't you find him?
- We will...

79
00:04:11.218 --> 00:04:14.279
That's what you keep saying.
That's what everyone keeps saying.

80
00:04:14.454 --> 00:04:16.719
You're the FBI. If you
can't find him. who can?

81
00:04:16.890 --> 00:04:18.324
Claire. Claire...

82
00:04:26.933 --> 00:04:28.424
How did Jordy kill himself?

83
00:04:28.602 --> 00:04:30.127
He choked.

84
00:04:30.303 --> 00:04:34.399
Pried the bandage loose
with his mouth and ate it.

85
00:04:34.574 --> 00:04:36.440
You certain Maggie
knows where Joey is?

86
00:04:36.610 --> 00:04:39.307
He said Emma and Maggie
were behind setting up the house.

87
00:04:39.479 --> 00:04:41.038
She'd know where they have Joey.

88
00:04:47.020 --> 00:04:49.922
Okay. Not that way. Straight...

89
00:04:50.123 --> 00:04:51.751
- I am going straight.
- No. no. no.

90
00:04:51.925 --> 00:04:54.451
- I know that it seems that way. but...
- You...

91
00:04:54.628 --> 00:04:57.792
You don't have to help me walk.

92
00:04:58.298 --> 00:04:59.698
I know how to walk.

93
00:05:04.271 --> 00:05:06.069
Well done.

94
00:05:08.308 --> 00:05:12.040
Oh. my God. What am
I going to do with you?

95
00:05:12.212 --> 00:05:15.273
I'm sorry I drank too much.

96
00:05:18.251 --> 00:05:20.049
- You gonna take that?
- No.

97
00:05:20.220 --> 00:05:23.156
I wanna talk to
Joe about Maggie.

98
00:05:32.332 --> 00:05:33.630
Ryan.

99
00:05:33.800 --> 00:05:35.291
Hello. Joe.

100
00:05:35.468 --> 00:05:38.028
- How can I help you today?
- I'm having a problem.

101
00:05:38.205 --> 00:05:40.367
I just can't see the
brilliance in all this.

102
00:05:40.540 --> 00:05:42.702
If you're writing a book.
where's the smarts?

103
00:05:42.876 --> 00:05:45.004
So far it just all seems
like amateur hour.

104
00:05:45.178 --> 00:05:49.809
You found these three unstable
freaks. you got Emma. Jacob. Paul.

105
00:05:49.983 --> 00:05:56.389
You convince them that to kill is to love or
live or whatever the hell you're preaching.

106
00:05:56.556 --> 00:05:58.081
You get them to kidnap your son.

107
00:05:58.258 --> 00:06:01.854
But it just seems beneath you
to go after such easy targets.

108
00:06:03.630 --> 00:06:05.258
I don't follow.

109
00:06:05.432 --> 00:06:07.094
<i>They're obviously screwed up.</i>

110
00:06:07.267 --> 00:06:09.759
Rick Kester's running
around wearing a Poe mask.

111
00:06:09.936 --> 00:06:12.030
It just all seems so silly.

112
00:06:12.205 --> 00:06:15.505
Yeah. I'll give you that one. I
was never a big fan of that idea.

113
00:06:15.675 --> 00:06:19.840
But I do appreciate
his wife. Maggie.

114
00:06:20.013 --> 00:06:23.279
- Maggie?
- I find her most interesting.

115
00:06:23.450 --> 00:06:25.351
And they are so in love.

116
00:06:26.052 --> 00:06:27.520
- As you know...
- Yeah.

117
00:06:27.687 --> 00:06:32.057
- I'm partial to a good love story.
- Well. that love story's come to an end.

118
00:06:34.628 --> 00:06:35.652
<i>Are they dead?</i>

119
00:06:36.429 --> 00:06:38.728
Rick is. Yeah. I
killed him myself.

120
00:06:40.567 --> 00:06:41.728
Oh. I...

121
00:06:41.902 --> 00:06:44.371
I'm delighted to hear that.

122
00:06:44.537 --> 00:06:48.167
You're getting your mojo
back. That's wonderful news.

123
00:06:49.276 --> 00:06:52.371
I don't suppose Maggie
was too pleased to hear that.

124
00:06:52.946 --> 00:06:54.881
Why's that?

125
00:06:57.550 --> 00:07:00.543
Oh. This is about Maggie.
You're on a fishing expedition.

126
00:07:00.720 --> 00:07:03.121
Why didn't you say? We
could've cut to the chase.

127
00:07:03.290 --> 00:07:05.759
Yes. Maggie... Maggie is...

128
00:07:07.093 --> 00:07:09.619
She is a very special girl.

129
00:07:09.796 --> 00:07:11.196
How so?

130
00:07:11.698 --> 00:07:14.668
Her real name is
Margaret Schuller.

131
00:07:14.834 --> 00:07:19.238
- That's S-C-H-U-L-L-E-R.
- Go get on that.

132
00:07:19.406 --> 00:07:22.342
She first visited
me eight years ago.

133
00:07:22.509 --> 00:07:24.705
She'd written to
me once or twice.

134
00:07:25.712 --> 00:07:30.741
It turned out she'd been on this
extraordinary killing spree in Arkansas...

135
00:07:30.917 --> 00:07:32.579
and completely got away with it.

136
00:07:33.586 --> 00:07:38.684
No. I find Maggie to be
extremely resourceful. tenacious...

137
00:07:38.858 --> 00:07:41.760
and impressive.

138
00:07:45.298 --> 00:07:48.632
'02 to '05. Little Rock.
Arkansas. there were six murders.

139
00:07:48.802 --> 00:07:51.601
Still unsolved. attributed
to a female serial killer.

140
00:07:51.771 --> 00:07:53.569
I remember this.
Victims were stabbed.

141
00:07:53.740 --> 00:07:56.767
Little Rock Homicide sent a
witness sketch. it's on my screen.

142
00:07:56.943 --> 00:07:59.003
They are not aware
of Margaret Schuller.

143
00:07:59.179 --> 00:08:02.274
If she visited Carroll in
prison. she used an alias.

144
00:08:05.018 --> 00:08:06.748
I need the phone. Where is it?

145
00:08:12.826 --> 00:08:14.192
Did you see the news?

146
00:08:14.361 --> 00:08:16.660
There's an APB on
Maggie. They can't find her.

147
00:08:18.031 --> 00:08:20.626
<i>- Leave a message.</i>
- She's not picking up.

148
00:08:20.800 --> 00:08:23.998
Maggie? Where are you?

149
00:08:24.304 --> 00:08:28.173
Call me. I'm worried. You
know the secure line. Call it.

150
00:08:29.342 --> 00:08:31.368
Something's wrong.
She should have called.

151
00:08:31.544 --> 00:08:32.978
Maybe she can't.

152
00:08:33.146 --> 00:08:34.705
That's what I'm worried about.

153
00:08:35.215 --> 00:08:37.150
Well. sounds like
Rick screwed up.

154
00:08:40.854 --> 00:08:41.913
Joey?

155
00:08:43.523 --> 00:08:45.583
I'm coming.

156
00:08:50.530 --> 00:08:52.897
- I'll be right out.
- Okay.

157
00:09:04.711 --> 00:09:06.339
What's happening
in the basement?

158
00:09:06.513 --> 00:09:10.314
Ask your boyfriend. He's
taking care of it. if he can.

159
00:09:10.884 --> 00:09:12.375
What is that supposed to mean?

160
00:09:12.552 --> 00:09:16.421
I lived with the guy for three years.
That's a long time to get to know someone.

161
00:09:16.589 --> 00:09:18.581
Is that about you two
getting your gay on?

162
00:09:18.758 --> 00:09:21.421
Look. I don't care how
much you fooled around.

163
00:09:21.594 --> 00:09:25.622
I'm not stupid. I know there's a reason
you were playing the jealous little bitch.

164
00:09:25.832 --> 00:09:30.463
But whatever happened. don't
fool yourself. Jacob's not gay.

165
00:09:30.637 --> 00:09:32.196
Try again. You are way off.

166
00:09:32.372 --> 00:09:34.307
This is about
Jacob and his lies.

167
00:09:34.474 --> 00:09:38.809
He's lied to you and me
and Joe and everyone else.

168
00:09:38.978 --> 00:09:40.241
About what?

169
00:09:42.615 --> 00:09:44.208
Jacob's never killed anyone.

170
00:09:45.919 --> 00:09:47.353
Ever.

171
00:09:48.254 --> 00:09:50.348
You didn't know that. did you?

172
00:09:53.126 --> 00:09:55.652
God. I wish you could
see your face right now.

173
00:10:03.803 --> 00:10:06.796
This is from a hardware store
off I-95 in Trenton. New Jersey.

174
00:10:07.373 --> 00:10:10.866
Now. they chat. something's
funny. they laugh and then...

175
00:10:14.914 --> 00:10:17.145
- What did she buy at the store?
- Cash purchase.

176
00:10:17.317 --> 00:10:20.810
Cord rope. tape. flashlight and
several magnets. Neo base magnets.

177
00:10:21.588 --> 00:10:23.420
Magnets? Chick's weird.

178
00:10:23.590 --> 00:10:26.856
If Joey was upstate. then I-95
would be the route that you'd take.

179
00:10:28.228 --> 00:10:31.426
Well. Forensics said
New York or Connecticut.

180
00:10:40.573 --> 00:10:43.634
You had a doctor's
appointment this morning. I called.

181
00:10:43.810 --> 00:10:46.336
They said that you missed
your last checkup too.

182
00:10:48.648 --> 00:10:50.617
You're a drunk with
a heart problem.

183
00:10:51.484 --> 00:10:54.784
You have a pacemaker sewn into
your chest to keep you alive. Ryan.

184
00:10:54.954 --> 00:10:57.617
You don't have
to take care of me.

185
00:11:02.862 --> 00:11:04.854
I care about you. I do.

186
00:11:05.031 --> 00:11:07.660
But I am just being stupid now.

187
00:11:07.834 --> 00:11:12.966
I mean. you've gotten a raw deal.
but something has to give here.

188
00:11:13.740 --> 00:11:16.369
Nothing changes
if nothing changes.

189
00:11:19.512 --> 00:11:22.710
What. is that a slogan from
one of your little groups?

190
00:11:29.889 --> 00:11:34.190
You know what? It hurts too
much to be around you. so I'm done.

191
00:11:40.333 --> 00:11:42.461
Sorry. gotta take this.

192
00:11:49.876 --> 00:11:50.935
Hello. Jenny.

193
00:11:51.110 --> 00:11:52.908
<i>Uh. Ryan?</i>

194
00:11:53.112 --> 00:11:56.378
- What's up? Everything
okay? JENNY: <i>No. No. it's not.</i>

195
00:11:58.818 --> 00:12:02.983
Hello. Ryan. It's Maggie Kester. Remember
me? The wife of the man you killed.

196
00:12:05.925 --> 00:12:08.019
Maggie. Where are you?

197
00:12:08.928 --> 00:12:10.396
What are you doing with Jenny?

198
00:12:10.563 --> 00:12:14.398
We're bonding. Since you've been too
busy to pick up the phone I won't keep you.

199
00:12:14.567 --> 00:12:17.696
I just have one question. how
do you want me to kill your sister?

200
00:12:23.576 --> 00:12:24.703
What do you want?

201
00:12:25.578 --> 00:12:26.910
I want you.

202
00:12:27.080 --> 00:12:31.916
I'll trade you for your sister's
life. But you come alone. Unarmed.

203
00:12:32.085 --> 00:12:36.648
If you bring any FBI
near here. your sister dies.

204
00:12:36.823 --> 00:12:39.418
- Does Joe know what you're doing?
<i>- I've gone off-book.</i>

205
00:12:39.592 --> 00:12:43.085
That's what killing a husband
will do to a girl. Come alone.

206
00:12:44.631 --> 00:12:45.655
Where are you?

207
00:12:45.832 --> 00:12:48.233
<i>Your sister promised to show
me how to make a good risotto.</i>

208
00:12:48.401 --> 00:12:50.233
<i>I'll save you some. Hurry.</i>

209
00:12:56.576 --> 00:12:57.976
You heard from Maggie?

210
00:12:58.911 --> 00:13:00.539
No.

211
00:13:02.248 --> 00:13:03.807
Are you getting worried?

212
00:13:03.983 --> 00:13:06.384
I'm more worried about
the girl in the basement.

213
00:13:07.487 --> 00:13:09.149
What are we going
to do about her?

214
00:13:14.994 --> 00:13:18.089
We can't let her go and I don't
want Joey to know about her.

215
00:13:18.698 --> 00:13:20.667
Take care of it.

216
00:13:23.436 --> 00:13:26.304
I mean. I really think
Paul should do it.

217
00:13:26.472 --> 00:13:28.134
He's the one that
brought her here.

218
00:13:28.308 --> 00:13:30.777
I think you should do it. Jacob.

219
00:13:31.778 --> 00:13:33.804
Since you never have.

220
00:13:39.185 --> 00:13:42.747
I dragged her body from
the car down to the water.

221
00:13:42.922 --> 00:13:47.417
That was the first time that I realized
how heavy bodies are when they're dead.

222
00:13:49.228 --> 00:13:54.428
I floated her out to the water
until just barely where I could stand.

223
00:13:56.969 --> 00:14:00.804
And I stood on
her for a good hour.

224
00:14:02.342 --> 00:14:07.440
Heh. I wanted to make sure her body
was completely weighted with water.

225
00:14:12.118 --> 00:14:13.245
And then I drove home.

226
00:14:24.831 --> 00:14:27.460
Who's next? Ha-ha-ha.

227
00:14:27.633 --> 00:14:30.865
You told that story about
the girl in high school.

228
00:14:31.037 --> 00:14:32.300
I'm sorry.

229
00:14:35.875 --> 00:14:37.241
I love you.

230
00:14:39.212 --> 00:14:40.942
And I was ashamed.

231
00:14:41.114 --> 00:14:44.744
I mean. I was the
only one who hadn't...

232
00:14:44.917 --> 00:14:46.647
Why be a part of this?

233
00:14:46.819 --> 00:14:48.378
Because I want to.

234
00:14:49.522 --> 00:14:52.390
I want to be a part of this.

235
00:14:54.394 --> 00:14:55.987
I tried.

236
00:15:01.334 --> 00:15:03.166
It's time to do more than try.

237
00:15:05.838 --> 00:15:07.306
Do it.

238
00:15:08.241 --> 00:15:11.643
- What's wrong?
- It's personal. I'll be back as soon as I can.

239
00:15:11.811 --> 00:15:14.906
You're lying. Tell me the truth.

240
00:15:15.882 --> 00:15:21.287
I have a personal matter that I
need to attend to. I will be back.

241
00:15:22.288 --> 00:15:26.055
- Uh. where's he going?
- I don't know. Go find out.

242
00:15:26.225 --> 00:15:29.252
You put me in the role of
snitch before. I didn't like it.

243
00:15:29.595 --> 00:15:32.759
He just took a call and now
he's out of here. Something's up.

244
00:15:32.932 --> 00:15:34.628
Well. who called him?

245
00:15:34.801 --> 00:15:35.928
Someone named Jenny.

246
00:15:43.342 --> 00:15:45.072
Where are you going so fast?

247
00:15:45.244 --> 00:15:48.339
- Parker tell you to follow me?
- Yeah. I'm starting to feel used.

248
00:15:48.514 --> 00:15:50.949
She thinks we bonded. we
both know you don't bond.

249
00:15:51.117 --> 00:15:53.086
So are you going to Brooklyn?

250
00:15:53.886 --> 00:15:55.821
Why would I be
going to Brooklyn?

251
00:15:56.522 --> 00:15:58.115
It's where your sister lives.

252
00:15:58.991 --> 00:16:02.655
Jenny Orson. 38. divorced.
runs a restaurant in Williamsburg.

253
00:16:02.829 --> 00:16:04.798
Is that where Maggie is?

254
00:16:05.531 --> 00:16:07.432
Does Parker know
where I'm going?

255
00:16:07.600 --> 00:16:09.228
Did Maggie threaten your sister?

256
00:16:14.674 --> 00:16:17.508
Maggie has Jenny. She
wants revenge for her husband.

257
00:16:17.677 --> 00:16:20.841
Everything Joe told us checks
out. She's a wanted serial killer.

258
00:16:21.013 --> 00:16:23.175
- You can't go on your own.
- It's my sister.

259
00:16:23.349 --> 00:16:26.251
So let me go with you. Please.

260
00:16:27.620 --> 00:16:30.818
I didn't tell Parker about Jenny.
She doesn't know anything.

261
00:16:33.025 --> 00:16:34.186
You'll be fired.

262
00:16:34.360 --> 00:16:37.023
I think I'm traumatized from
the loss of a fellow agent.

263
00:16:37.196 --> 00:16:38.824
I'm not thinking clearly.

264
00:16:38.998 --> 00:16:41.263
Probably get off with a warning.

265
00:16:45.771 --> 00:16:46.795
Okay.

266
00:17:00.820 --> 00:17:02.311
My name is Mike. sir.

267
00:17:03.256 --> 00:17:07.318
You keep calling me Weston. That's
my last name. My first name is Mike.

268
00:17:11.030 --> 00:17:12.089
So your sister. Jenny?

269
00:17:13.199 --> 00:17:15.100
Are you two close?

270
00:17:16.102 --> 00:17:17.263
It's complicated.

271
00:17:18.604 --> 00:17:21.233
Copy that. I got three brothers.

272
00:17:21.407 --> 00:17:24.571
Close with one.
hate the other two.

273
00:17:26.913 --> 00:17:30.748
No? Nothing? No
conversation at all?

274
00:17:33.085 --> 00:17:35.054
It's a long way to
Brooklyn. that's all.

275
00:17:37.924 --> 00:17:40.553
- I'm glad you came.
- And surprised.

276
00:17:40.726 --> 00:17:42.251
Yeah. I'm surprised.

277
00:17:42.428 --> 00:17:44.090
Me too.

278
00:17:44.363 --> 00:17:47.231
- But I'm more glad.
- Me too.

279
00:17:55.675 --> 00:17:58.907
- And then they get mad.
- No.

280
00:18:00.413 --> 00:18:02.405
- There she is.
- Sorry to keep you waiting.

281
00:18:02.582 --> 00:18:03.845
- How you doing? Hi.
- Hi.

282
00:18:04.016 --> 00:18:06.349
Claire. this is Jenny.
my sister. Jenny. Claire.

283
00:18:06.519 --> 00:18:08.920
- Hi. It's nice to meet you.
- Hi. Nice to meet you.

284
00:18:09.088 --> 00:18:12.684
- I love your restaurant.
- It's yours. Take the mortgage. Take it all.

285
00:18:15.828 --> 00:18:18.662
- So do we get menus. or...?
- No. this is a special occasion.

286
00:18:18.831 --> 00:18:22.666
I have a whole menu prepared.
I hope you like salmon. Say yes.

287
00:18:23.703 --> 00:18:26.605
- I love salmon.
- She's winning me over.

288
00:18:35.848 --> 00:18:37.544
It's Parker.

289
00:19:05.645 --> 00:19:06.840
So. what's the plan?

290
00:19:07.013 --> 00:19:11.678
My sister's restaurant is a few blocks up.
It's closed. I'm gonna do whatever Maggie says.

291
00:19:11.851 --> 00:19:14.821
The moment I know my sister
is safe. I don't care after that.

292
00:19:15.588 --> 00:19:17.489
You need a better
plan. Take my gun.

293
00:19:17.657 --> 00:19:18.989
No. she said come unarmed.

294
00:19:19.158 --> 00:19:21.718
- Are you a good shot?
- I'm an overachiever. sir.

295
00:19:21.894 --> 00:19:24.989
There's a kitchen door. side
alley. I'm gonna leave it unlocked.

296
00:19:25.164 --> 00:19:29.260
Something happens. you don't worry
about me. you make it all about Jenny.

297
00:19:29.435 --> 00:19:31.267
You understand?

298
00:19:31.771 --> 00:19:33.364
Yeah.

299
00:21:45.638 --> 00:21:47.106
Hello. Ryan.

300
00:21:47.807 --> 00:21:49.139
I'm here. Maggie.

301
00:21:49.742 --> 00:21:51.608
- Where's my sister?
- She's here.

302
00:21:51.777 --> 00:21:53.746
Don't do that. Or she dies.

303
00:21:53.913 --> 00:21:59.910
Okay. okay. You got
me. Just let her go.

304
00:22:00.085 --> 00:22:01.849
I intend to.

305
00:22:02.054 --> 00:22:04.182
I've grown fond of your sister.

306
00:22:04.356 --> 00:22:06.348
She loves you very much...

307
00:22:06.559 --> 00:22:11.293
and I've enjoyed getting to know all
about Ryan Hardy. the early years.

308
00:22:11.463 --> 00:22:15.332
It's a very sad story.

309
00:22:15.501 --> 00:22:16.833
Where is she?

310
00:22:17.336 --> 00:22:18.998
Jenny?

311
00:22:20.339 --> 00:22:21.967
Jenny?

312
00:22:22.441 --> 00:22:23.773
Jenny!

313
00:22:23.943 --> 00:22:25.673
Ryan!

314
00:22:30.149 --> 00:22:32.948
Don't scream. Okay?

315
00:22:40.359 --> 00:22:41.383
Thank you.

316
00:22:51.804 --> 00:22:53.397
Thank you.

317
00:22:58.711 --> 00:23:00.737
- Jacob. right?
- No talking.

318
00:23:01.847 --> 00:23:03.873
I'll be quiet.

319
00:23:06.252 --> 00:23:08.983
I just want to say one thing.

320
00:23:10.155 --> 00:23:14.058
If you let me go. I won't
say anything to anyone.

321
00:23:14.226 --> 00:23:15.524
Of course you won't.

322
00:23:15.694 --> 00:23:17.686
I know you don't
want to hurt me.

323
00:23:20.900 --> 00:23:23.369
Look. I have an idea.

324
00:23:23.836 --> 00:23:26.567
You can cut me a little bit.

325
00:23:26.739 --> 00:23:29.174
On my arms and my legs.

326
00:23:29.341 --> 00:23:32.641
And I'll bleed a lot.
All over the place.

327
00:23:33.145 --> 00:23:35.705
And then you can tell
your friends you killed me.

328
00:23:35.881 --> 00:23:38.510
Then you can say that you
took me out to the woods...

329
00:23:38.684 --> 00:23:41.449
- and dumped me in the ravine.
- They won't believe that.

330
00:23:41.654 --> 00:23:44.556
You'll make them believe it.

331
00:23:44.723 --> 00:23:51.254
And then I'll go home. I
won't tell anyone. Not a soul.

332
00:23:51.897 --> 00:23:53.525
Please.

333
00:23:56.268 --> 00:23:59.864
Let me go!

334
00:24:00.906 --> 00:24:03.307
I don't want to die.

335
00:24:10.249 --> 00:24:12.275
What's wrong. Jacob?

336
00:24:13.919 --> 00:24:16.184
I don't want to disappoint you.

337
00:24:17.823 --> 00:24:20.088
I tried...

338
00:24:22.094 --> 00:24:26.327
I can't do it.

339
00:24:27.499 --> 00:24:28.967
Oh.

340
00:24:30.402 --> 00:24:32.667
Do the others know?

341
00:24:32.838 --> 00:24:34.602
I lied.

342
00:24:35.708 --> 00:24:36.937
I know that I shouldn't...

343
00:24:37.109 --> 00:24:39.078
Jacob.

344
00:24:41.780 --> 00:24:44.079
Do you want to be a part of us?

345
00:24:44.249 --> 00:24:48.152
Very much so. I don't want
to go back to my old life.

346
00:24:48.320 --> 00:24:50.482
I can't.

347
00:24:52.658 --> 00:24:56.925
<i>Deep into that darkness peering</i>

348
00:24:57.529 --> 00:25:03.992
<i>Long I stood there
wondering. fearing</i>

349
00:25:04.169 --> 00:25:11.008
<i>Dreaming dreams no mortal
Ever dared to dream before</i>

350
00:25:12.144 --> 00:25:13.271
It's okay.

351
00:25:14.546 --> 00:25:17.812
No one need know.
It'll be our secret.

352
00:25:17.983 --> 00:25:19.383
But I want to.

353
00:25:19.551 --> 00:25:21.144
I know.

354
00:25:21.320 --> 00:25:24.017
And one day you will.

355
00:25:25.357 --> 00:25:28.691
But when you are ready.

356
00:25:29.928 --> 00:25:31.453
Hmm?

357
00:25:32.264 --> 00:25:34.824
Please.

358
00:26:07.499 --> 00:26:11.937
Shut up. Shut up.

359
00:26:16.241 --> 00:26:20.372
Come on. Wake up. that's it.

360
00:26:21.180 --> 00:26:24.116
Easy. you don't want
to tip. That could hurt.

361
00:26:26.518 --> 00:26:29.249
Jenny? Did she hurt you?

362
00:26:29.421 --> 00:26:32.016
No. I didn't.

363
00:26:32.191 --> 00:26:34.558
We were waiting for you.

364
00:26:34.726 --> 00:26:37.423
- Right. Jenny?
- Oh. yeah.

365
00:26:50.776 --> 00:26:52.745
Jenny.

366
00:26:53.078 --> 00:26:55.274
You're gonna be okay.

367
00:26:56.115 --> 00:26:58.607
I don't know about Jenny here.

368
00:26:59.818 --> 00:27:01.844
You promised me.

369
00:27:02.020 --> 00:27:04.615
I'm not going to kill her...

370
00:27:05.424 --> 00:27:12.422
but the psychological damage
of watching her brother die...

371
00:27:12.664 --> 00:27:15.429
is bound to leave a few scars.

372
00:27:15.601 --> 00:27:18.093
Tell me what to do. Just
please tell me what to do.

373
00:27:18.270 --> 00:27:21.502
It should be Claire who witnesses
your last breath. but. well...

374
00:27:21.673 --> 00:27:23.801
she's locked up
tighter than Joe Carroll.

375
00:27:23.976 --> 00:27:27.105
Claire would have been a
more appropriate choice. but...

376
00:27:27.279 --> 00:27:30.010
oh. well. pain is pain.

377
00:27:35.988 --> 00:27:38.719
You know. I really enjoyed
meeting your sister today.

378
00:27:38.924 --> 00:27:40.790
Good. I'm glad.

379
00:27:40.959 --> 00:27:47.559
I feel like I got a little more insight
into the mystery that is Ryan Hardy.

380
00:27:47.733 --> 00:27:49.793
Not much. just... Just a sliver.

381
00:27:49.968 --> 00:27:53.666
- A sliver. huh?
- Yeah. just a sliver.

382
00:27:57.042 --> 00:28:01.480
So I just gave you
a really good in...

383
00:28:01.647 --> 00:28:07.177
to open up and talk to
me. and you didn't take it.

384
00:28:13.325 --> 00:28:17.660
Come on. Ryan. just talk to me.

385
00:28:18.830 --> 00:28:20.492
It's kind of a downer.

386
00:28:20.666 --> 00:28:23.898
- I don't care.
- Yeah.

387
00:28:24.503 --> 00:28:26.495
All right.

388
00:28:27.472 --> 00:28:29.737
You asked for it.

389
00:28:29.908 --> 00:28:33.401
My mom got sick when
I was a kid. Leukemia.

390
00:28:33.579 --> 00:28:37.949
And she fought for
years. but it got her.

391
00:28:38.116 --> 00:28:40.745
- She died when I was 14.
- Ryan. I...

392
00:28:40.919 --> 00:28:45.619
My dad. uh. was a street cop...

393
00:28:45.791 --> 00:28:50.422
Albany P.D. his entire
life until he retired.

394
00:28:51.196 --> 00:28:54.724
One night he walked into
the wrong corner store...

395
00:28:54.900 --> 00:28:57.529
at the wrong time
and tried to be a hero.

396
00:28:57.703 --> 00:29:00.867
Ryan. I'm... I'm so sorry.

397
00:29:02.574 --> 00:29:06.238
So it's just you and Jenny then?

398
00:29:08.113 --> 00:29:11.914
We had an older brother. Ray.

399
00:29:14.286 --> 00:29:16.812
New York fireman.

400
00:29:17.222 --> 00:29:20.750
- Oh... If you say 9/11...
- Okay. I won't say it.

401
00:29:24.162 --> 00:29:25.824
I told you it was a downer.

402
00:29:30.669 --> 00:29:32.968
- You and death go way back.
- Hmm.

403
00:29:33.138 --> 00:29:35.073
A lot farther than Joe.

404
00:30:10.142 --> 00:30:13.169
Go. Get out of here.

405
00:30:14.579 --> 00:30:16.605
Go!

406
00:30:30.595 --> 00:30:33.292
<i>Are trying to end a
recent murder spree...</i>

407
00:30:33.465 --> 00:30:35.730
<i>that looks to be the
work of a secret cult...</i>

408
00:30:35.901 --> 00:30:40.805
<i>loyal to serial killer Joe Carroll. Several
people are dead. and Carroll's son Joey...</i>

409
00:30:47.679 --> 00:30:50.649
It's the girl. She's
getting away.

410
00:31:08.500 --> 00:31:11.493
You go that way. I'll
go around the back.

411
00:31:43.301 --> 00:31:45.236
Paul.

412
00:32:11.563 --> 00:32:14.692
Relax. it's only a flesh wound.

413
00:32:30.449 --> 00:32:34.978
One of my foster dads...

414
00:32:35.153 --> 00:32:40.956
he had a pacemaker
just like yours.

415
00:32:41.660 --> 00:32:45.961
I read your book. I know
how bad off your heart is.

416
00:32:46.131 --> 00:32:48.532
You really need it.

417
00:32:49.768 --> 00:32:54.035
Did you know
electromagnetic fields...

418
00:32:54.239 --> 00:32:57.641
can interrupt the
function of a pacemaker?

419
00:32:57.809 --> 00:33:01.041
- No! No!
- Shh!

420
00:33:01.246 --> 00:33:04.182
All you have to do is watch.
You have the easy part. Jenny.

421
00:33:04.349 --> 00:33:06.375
But your brother...

422
00:33:06.551 --> 00:33:10.352
he is probably...

423
00:33:10.856 --> 00:33:17.160
starting to feel a little woozy.

424
00:33:17.329 --> 00:33:19.696
Let her go.

425
00:33:20.031 --> 00:33:24.969
Please. Please don't...
Please don't do that to Jenny.

426
00:33:25.704 --> 00:33:27.696
You can kill me.
but please let her go.

427
00:33:27.873 --> 00:33:32.811
Do you really think she's
going to walk out of here?

428
00:33:32.978 --> 00:33:35.311
There's too many knives
in this place for that.

429
00:33:35.480 --> 00:33:37.176
- No. no.
- We're off-book.

430
00:33:37.349 --> 00:33:39.079
- No.
- Remember?

431
00:33:39.284 --> 00:33:40.343
It's improv night.

432
00:33:40.519 --> 00:33:44.422
- Joe doesn't want you to kill me.
- That's the beauty of it.

433
00:33:44.589 --> 00:33:47.559
I'm not killing you. Joe is.

434
00:33:47.726 --> 00:33:54.530
He's the one who stabbed your heart.
I'm just shutting down your heart gizmo...

435
00:33:54.699 --> 00:34:00.161
so that Joe actually does
kill you. I think it's perfect.

436
00:34:01.439 --> 00:34:02.873
Jenny. you watching...

437
00:34:04.943 --> 00:34:08.311
how cursed your family is?

438
00:34:13.218 --> 00:34:19.283
This is for Rick. We
loved each other.

439
00:34:19.457 --> 00:34:23.690
Do you even
understand love. Ryan?

440
00:34:23.862 --> 00:34:26.696
Real love?

441
00:34:37.676 --> 00:34:39.167
Oh.

442
00:34:39.344 --> 00:34:43.406
Your fingers are blue.
Your blood's not circulating.

443
00:34:52.257 --> 00:34:54.419
Hurts. doesn't it?

444
00:34:54.593 --> 00:34:56.152
No. no!

445
00:34:59.497 --> 00:35:02.592
- Unh!
- No! No!

446
00:35:04.369 --> 00:35:06.429
It'll be soon now.

447
00:35:09.074 --> 00:35:11.634
You don't want to miss the end.

448
00:35:13.578 --> 00:35:16.878
Let's get closer so you
can see his last breath.

449
00:35:22.087 --> 00:35:24.318
Stop.

450
00:35:34.132 --> 00:35:36.033
Okay. hey.

451
00:35:36.201 --> 00:35:37.931
Hey. come on.

452
00:35:38.103 --> 00:35:41.301
You okay? Come on. wake up.

453
00:35:41.473 --> 00:35:43.635
All right. Okay.

454
00:35:52.851 --> 00:35:55.719
- I'm sorry. I didn't hear anyone.
- I was just cleaning up.

455
00:35:55.920 --> 00:35:57.411
Yeah. same here.

456
00:35:58.690 --> 00:36:01.922
She really found
the mud. didn't she?

457
00:36:12.437 --> 00:36:14.338
We both love him. Paul.

458
00:36:16.641 --> 00:36:18.974
I know that's hard for you.

459
00:36:22.247 --> 00:36:25.843
Come on. let's
get you cleaned up.

460
00:36:32.057 --> 00:36:35.494
Don't freak out. It's not
like we're going to get it on.

461
00:37:41.126 --> 00:37:42.253
Your pacing is normal.

462
00:37:42.427 --> 00:37:45.920
Once you remove the interference.
it diverts back to its normal function.

463
00:37:46.097 --> 00:37:49.397
- Good to know.
- Make an appointment with your cardiologist.

464
00:37:49.567 --> 00:37:52.537
- You okay?
- Yeah. you?

465
00:37:53.071 --> 00:37:57.065
Maggie Kester's cell phone. It
was on her. I got calls. e-mails.

466
00:37:57.242 --> 00:37:58.835
Thought it was
on a secure server.

467
00:37:59.043 --> 00:38:02.810
If there was a delay on an incoming
and an outgoing. I can pull a location.

468
00:38:02.981 --> 00:38:06.179
- Does Parker know?
- Oh. yeah. She still chewed my ass out.

469
00:38:07.118 --> 00:38:08.609
I'll get suspended over this.

470
00:38:09.621 --> 00:38:11.681
We should go. I gotta get back.

471
00:38:11.856 --> 00:38:15.156
Yeah. Mike. just give
me one minute. okay?

472
00:38:15.326 --> 00:38:16.817
I'll be right with you.

473
00:38:22.934 --> 00:38:27.133
Do you think you could disappear for
a while? I think it would be a good idea.

474
00:38:27.305 --> 00:38:28.773
Yeah.

475
00:38:28.940 --> 00:38:30.841
Uh. Miami's called
once or twice.

476
00:38:32.811 --> 00:38:34.279
Maybe a visit's in order.

477
00:38:35.213 --> 00:38:36.772
Okay.

478
00:38:39.851 --> 00:38:40.875
How's Claire?

479
00:38:43.054 --> 00:38:46.422
- So. what happened?
- Told her I needed time.

480
00:38:49.360 --> 00:38:51.795
We were never going to
work. You said so yourself.

481
00:38:51.963 --> 00:38:53.727
Until I saw you guys.

482
00:38:53.898 --> 00:38:57.801
I mean. it's weird. the situation.
but I saw you guys. I was wrong.

483
00:38:57.969 --> 00:38:59.995
You love her.

484
00:39:00.705 --> 00:39:02.799
I'm well aware of that. Jen.

485
00:39:05.210 --> 00:39:08.977
So you break up with her
in some gesture of nobility?

486
00:39:09.147 --> 00:39:12.549
Claire and her son
need to move forward.

487
00:39:12.717 --> 00:39:16.245
As long as I am there. I am always
going to be a part of Joe Carroll.

488
00:39:16.421 --> 00:39:18.413
She needs a new
start. She deserves that.

489
00:39:18.623 --> 00:39:20.615
What do you deserve?

490
00:39:24.762 --> 00:39:27.163
She's hanging in there.

491
00:39:29.267 --> 00:39:34.069
You know that woman
tonight was right about us.

492
00:39:34.239 --> 00:39:38.677
Our family has been
cursed somehow.

493
00:39:38.843 --> 00:39:42.041
Surrounded by death.

494
00:39:43.681 --> 00:39:46.378
I know that you're afraid to
let anyone get close to you.

495
00:39:46.551 --> 00:39:48.452
It's who we are.

496
00:39:50.054 --> 00:39:52.649
But we can't go
through life alone.

497
00:39:52.957 --> 00:39:55.290
That's no life.

498
00:39:58.429 --> 00:39:59.920
Emma?

499
00:40:01.466 --> 00:40:04.664
I'm sorry about...

500
00:40:11.409 --> 00:40:13.571
We're not giving up on you.

501
00:40:33.998 --> 00:40:39.198
When will you know? Let me
know as soon as you do. Thanks.

502
00:40:46.444 --> 00:40:48.106
Hey.

503
00:40:48.780 --> 00:40:51.750
That woman I went after.
we got her cell phone.

504
00:40:51.916 --> 00:40:55.648
They were able to find a signal in
upstate New York. Dutchess County.

505
00:40:58.656 --> 00:41:02.855
- I'm glad your sister is okay.
- Thanks.

506
00:41:03.027 --> 00:41:06.486
Cyber team thinks they're gonna
have an address. two hours at the most.

507
00:41:07.799 --> 00:41:09.791
This is a break. Claire.

508
00:41:09.968 --> 00:41:11.527
We're gonna find Joey.

509
00:41:13.304 --> 00:41:15.000
I know you will.

510
00:41:19.177 --> 00:41:20.270
I... I should go.

511
00:41:20.445 --> 00:41:24.143
No. you need to... You need to rest.
You need something to eat. I can...

512
00:41:24.315 --> 00:41:26.250
I can make you something.

513
00:41:29.053 --> 00:41:30.544
What do you deserve?

514
00:41:35.660 --> 00:41:36.821
I'm not ready.

515
00:41:36.995 --> 00:41:39.624
Life doesn't wait for
you. You've got to jump in.

516
00:41:39.797 --> 00:41:42.995
Claire's not ready. She's been
through too much. She has a kid.

517
00:41:43.668 --> 00:41:47.901
I can make you breakfast.
It's no trouble. Just...

518
00:41:51.542 --> 00:41:53.807
Just... Just until they call.

519
00:41:54.145 --> 00:41:55.636
<i>We're not talking about Claire.</i>

520
00:41:55.813 --> 00:41:59.045
I'm no good for
her or for her son.

521
00:41:59.217 --> 00:42:02.551
I am a constant reminder
of the worst time in her life...

522
00:42:02.720 --> 00:42:04.882
and she doesn't deserve that.

523
00:42:05.056 --> 00:42:09.892
- But you love her.
- Because I love her.

524
00:42:12.430 --> 00:42:13.898
Ryan. stay.

525
00:42:14.665 --> 00:42:16.065
Please.

526
00:42:23.074 --> 00:42:25.373
I really need to get back.

527
00:42:27.412 --> 00:42:29.847
I'll call you as soon
as I know anything.

527
